  <!-- Introducción de la lección (narrative) -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="narrative-leccion-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>Students use the cube towers from the previous lesson. They may notice that the tower and number just before the given number shows one less and the tower and number just after the given number shows one more. Students also discuss how to use the count sequence to identify one less and one more than a given number.</p>
<p>In the lesson synthesis, students practice saying the verbal count sequence to 20. Add variety to the counting by adding movement. For example, students can count as they clap, stomp their feet, or jump.</p>
  </paragraphs>
  
  <!-- Preguntas de reflexión profesor -->
  <paragraphs>
    <title><custom ref="reflection-quest-titulo"/></title>
    <p>[+++++++++++++++]</p>
    <p>In future lessons, students will compare written numbers 1-10. How does the work with one more and one less help prepare students for this work?</p>
  </paragraphs>
</introduction>


